race.comment: HEDGED (4) brings the best form into this. He was just nosed out fresh by Jigsaw who subsequently won a G2 next time out, before being held up down the straight in the G3 Rising Fast behind Caballus. He ran the second-fastest final 200m of that race and probably finishes third with clear air earlier. Back to 1100m no issue, he tags the speed and can prove too strong late. That speed will come in the form of BEAST MODE (6) who has lived up to his name with the blinkers applied his past two. They've been at Moonee Valley over 955m and 1000m, this is a different test, he'll look the winner at the 100m mark but may be vulnerable late. SGHIRRIPA (2) did enough fresh in the G2 Caulfield Sprint and will be fitter. His best form would go close. TIGER SHARK (3) is back in a more suitable race having won well over this route three back. BOSTON ROCKS (10) is coming through some good Sydney races, can figure.
